text: Komárom-Esztergom is an administrative county in Hungary. The capital of Komárom-Esztergom county is Tatabánya. It is in the northwestern part of the country. It borders with the Hungarian counties of Fejér, Győr-Moson-Sopron, Pest and Veszprém and the Slovakian region of Nitra. In 2019, 299,207 people lived there. Its area is 2,265 km².
title: Komárom-Esztergom County
